The paper presents a low-cost robot with a navigation system based on vision, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The navigation system uses optical flow pattern recognition, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of an SVM-based classifier, which is a common machine learning algorithm (cs.AI). The evaluation of the system's performance involves analyzing a dataset, which could fall under the category of machine learning or data analysis (cs.LG). Finally, the system is designed to be autonomous, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
